name: WebResource
desc: A WebResource object represents a downloaded URL. It encapsulates the data of the download as well as other resource properties such as the URL, MIME type, and frame name.

items.name: init!(data: Data!, url: URL!, mimeType: String!, textEncodingName: String!, frameName: String!)
items.desc: Initializes and returns a web resource instance.

items.name: var frameName: String!
items.desc: The name of the frame. If the receiver does not represent the contents of an entire HTML frame, this is nil.
